Based on my analysis of the codebase, I have identified exactly where these issues are occurring and how to fix them.

1. Login Redirect Failure (Page Reloads)
Where the issue is:

File: 

frontend/src/pages/login.rs
Method: 

Login()
 component and handle_login closure.
Lines of Code: Line 24 (evt.prevent_default();) and Line 54 (onsubmit: handle_login).
The Issue: In Dioxus, calling evt.prevent_default() inside the event handler closure is not sufficient to prevent the browser from executing a native form submission. As a result, when you hit "Submit", the browser performs a traditional POST/GET request, which triggers a full page reload and bypasses your async API and SPA routing logic. Furthermore, the redirect currently uses window.location().set_href("/dashboard") which intentionally forces a page refresh rather than leveraging Dioxus's client-side router.

Possible Fix:

You must apply the special prevent_default: "onsubmit" attribute directly to the <form> macro in your rsx!.
Replace window.location manipulation with the built-in Dioxus use_navigator() hook for clean, immediate SPA redirects.

// In frontend/src/pages/login.rs

// 1. Add navigator hook at the top of Login()
let nav = use_navigator(); 

let handle_login = move |evt: Event<FormData>| {
    // You can remove evt.prevent_default() here
    spawn(async move {
        // ... api call ...
        match api::login(&username.read(), &password.read()).await {
            Ok(resp) => {
                api::set_token(&resp.data.token);
                *AUTH.write() = AuthState::logged_in(resp.data.user);

                // 2. Use Dioxus navigator instead of window.location
                nav.push(crate::Route::Dashboard {});
            }
            // ...
        }
    });
};

// 3. Update the form rsx! to include the prevent_default attribute
rsx! {
    form { 
        class: "login-form", 
        onsubmit: handle_login,
        prevent_default: "onsubmit", // <-- ADD THIS LINE

        // ... inputs
    }
}

2. Protected Routes (Dashboard) Accessible Without Auth
Where the issue is:

File: 

frontend/src/layouts/mod.rs
 (MainLayout)
Method: 

MainLayout()
Lines of Code: Lines 12-17 (use_effect routing block).
The Issue: Your routing architecture correctly wraps /dashboard inside 

MainLayout
. However, the authorization guard use_effect only redirects to /login if both !auth.is_authenticated && !api::is_logged_in() evaluate to true. If a user has a dead/stale token inside their LocalStorage (which makes api::is_logged_in() return true), the redirect will fail to fire.

The Dioxus Router handles renders quickly; if the use_effect doesn't enforce the redirect immediately (or if it gets confused by a stale local token), it can trap the user in the layout/spinner state or let parts of the page slip through before hydration finishes.

Possible Fix: Update the 

MainLayout
 to ensure that any unauthenticated access unequivocally replaces the route with the Login route. If 

is_logged_in()
 returns false, it should immediately kick them out.

 // In frontend/src/layouts/mod.rs
use_effect(move || {
    let auth = AUTH.read();
    let has_token = api::is_logged_in();

    // If they aren't authenticated and they don't even have a token, kick them.
    if !has_token {
        nav.replace(crate::Route::Login {});
    } 
    // If they have a token, but hydration ran and rejected it (logged_out state)
    else if has_token && !auth.is_authenticated && !auth.is_loading {
        nav.replace(crate::Route::Login {});
    }
});

(Note: If you make the fixes above, the Dioxus router will correctly grab the event, stop the page from hard-reloading, securely negotiate your backend JWT in the background, and seamlessly display the internal Dashboard.)

