This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:

The session addressed multiple sequential issues on the CampusLearn Operations Suite (Rust/Rocket backend, Dioxus/WASM frontend, MySQL 8.0):

1. **Auth flow bugs**: Login redirected back to login page; `/dashboard` accessible without auth; API returned 401 on protected pages
2. **Sign-in button reloaded page**: Clicking Sign In cleared inputs and reloaded instead of navigating to dashboard
3. **VPS Docker build OOM**: `cargo install trunk` was killed by OOM when compiling `lightningcss` on low-RAM VPS
4. **12 security/quality issues**: Booking cancel ownership bypass (`&& false` bug), course draft visibility, CORS permissiveness, dormant `ReauthRequired`/`HmacVerified` guards, background jobs not wired, mocked webhook delivery, missing tests
5. **HTTPS compliance**: Add TLS termination via proxy service, HTTP→HTTPS redirect, self-signed dev certs, update docs

---

2. Key Technical Concepts:

- **Dioxus 0.6** WASM frontend with `GlobalSignal<AuthState>`, `use_navigator()`, `use_effect` reactive tracking
- **Rocket 0.5** request guards: `AuthenticatedUser`, `ReauthRequired`, `HmacVerified`, `AdminGuard`, `CourseAuthorGuard`
- `prevent_default: "onsubmit"` RSX attribute (vs `evt.prevent_default()` in handler — Dioxus WASM requires the RSX form)
- SPA navigation via `nav.push(Route::Dashboard {})` vs hard reload via `window.location().set_href()`
- Dioxus reactive signal behavior: reading a signal inside `use_effect` makes effect re-run on signal changes; captured `bool` values do NOT create reactive dependencies
- Writing to a signal inside a `use_effect` that reads the same signal causes an infinite reactive loop
- Background jobs via `tokio::spawn` with `tokio::time::interval` loops
- HMAC-SHA256 request signing guard (`HmacVerified`) for machine-to-machine endpoints
- `ReauthRequired` guard enforcing recent credential re-verification (15-minute window)
- nginx TLS termination: HTTP 301 redirect to HTTPS, `ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3`, self-signed cert via `openssl req -x509`
- Object-level authorization (IDOR prevention)
- CORS: `AllowedOrigins::some_exact` vs `AllowedOrigins::all()` with credentials

---

3. Files and Code Sections:

**`frontend/src/pages/login.rs`** — Fixed form submission and navigation
- Added `let nav = use_navigator();` at component top
- Changed handler signature to `|_evt: Event<FormData>|` (prevent_default moved to RSX)
- Added `prevent_default: "onsubmit"` to form RSX attribute
- Replaced `window.location().set_href("/dashboard")` with `nav.push(crate::Route::Dashboard {})`
```rust
let nav = use_navigator();
let handle_login = move |_evt: Event<FormData>| {
    spawn(async move {
        // ...
        Ok(resp) => {
            api::set_token(&resp.data.token);
            *AUTH.write() = AuthState::logged_in(resp.data.user);
            nav.push(crate::Route::Dashboard {});
        }
    });
};
// In RSX:
form { class: "login-form", onsubmit: handle_login, prevent_default: "onsubmit", ... }
```

**`frontend/src/main.rs`** — Route restructuring, App hydration fix, Home component
- Moved `#[route("/login")] Login {}` outside `#[layout(layouts::MainLayout)]` block (after `#[end_layout]`)
- Removed `auth::AUTH.write().is_loading = true` from App's use_effect (caused reactive loop)
- Kept `*auth::AUTH.write() = auth::AuthState::logged_out()` in Err branch (bug fix)
- Added `mod jobs;` declaration
- Added CORS fix: `AllowedOrigins::some_exact(&[&allowed_origin])` with `ALLOWED_ORIGIN` env var
- Added two `tokio::spawn` background job loops
- Changed Home component to use `navigator()` instead of `window.location().set_href()`
```rust
#[component]
fn Home() -> Element {
    let nav = navigator();
    if api::is_logged_in() {
        nav.replace(Route::Dashboard {});
    } else {
        nav.replace(Route::Login {});
    }
    rsx! { div { class: "loading-container", p { "Redirecting..." } } }
}
```

Background jobs wiring:
```rust
let pool_jobs = pool.clone();
tokio::spawn(async move {
    let mut interval = tokio::time::interval(std::time::Duration::from_secs(60));
    loop {
        interval.tick().await;
        let _ = jobs::run_scheduled_transitions(&pool_jobs).await;
        let _ = jobs::run_risk_evaluation(&pool_jobs).await;
        let _ = jobs::process_webhooks(&pool_jobs).await;
    }
});
let pool_cleanup = pool.clone();
tokio::spawn(async move {
    let mut interval = tokio::time::interval(std::time::Duration::from_secs(3600));
    loop {
        interval.tick().await;
        let _ = jobs::cleanup_expired_data(&pool_cleanup).await;
    }
});
```

**`frontend/src/layouts/mod.rs`** — Auth guard (fully rewritten)
- `use_navigator()` at top
- `use_effect` reads `AUTH.read()` inside closure (makes it reactive)
- `if has_token && !auth.is_authenticated` → show "Loading session..." spinner
- `if !auth.is_authenticated` → show spinner while redirect effect fires
- Only renders full sidebar + Outlet when `auth.is_authenticated == true`
```rust
pub fn MainLayout() -> Element {
    let nav = use_navigator();
    use_effect(move || {
        let auth = AUTH.read();
        if !auth.is_authenticated && !api::is_logged_in() {
            nav.replace(crate::Route::Login {});
        }
    });
    let auth = AUTH.read();
    let has_token = api::is_logged_in();
    if has_token && !auth.is_authenticated {
        return rsx! { div { class: "app-container", main { class: "main-content",
            LoadingSpinner { message: "Loading session..." } } } };
    }
    if !auth.is_authenticated {
        return rsx! { div { class: "app-container", main { class: "main-content",
            LoadingSpinner {} } } };
    }
    // ... full authenticated layout with sidebar ...
}
```

**`frontend/Dockerfile`** — Pre-built trunk binary (VPS OOM fix)
```dockerfile
RUN curl -fsSL https://github.com/trunk-rs/trunk/releases/download/v0.21.5/trunk-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz \
    | tar -xzC /usr/local/bin
```

**`frontend/nginx.conf`** — Added security headers
```nginx
add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains" always;
add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff" always;
add_header X-Frame-Options "DENY" always;
add_header Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin" always;
```

**`backend/src/services/booking_service.rs`** — Fixed `cancel_booking` ownership
- Signature: `pub async fn cancel_booking(pool, booking_uuid, user_id: i64, role: &str, correlation_id)`
- Fixed: `if booking.booked_by != user_id && role != "admin"` (was `&& false`)

**`backend/src/routes/bookings.rs`** — Pass role to service
```rust
booking_service::cancel_booking(pool.inner(), &uuid, user.claims.user_id, &user.claims.role, None)
```

**`backend/src/services/course_service.rs`** — Added visibility check to `get_course`
```rust
pub async fn get_course(pool, uuid, role: &str, user_id: i64, department_id: Option<i64>) -> Result<CourseResponse, AppError> {
    let course = course_repo::find_course_by_uuid(pool, uuid).await?
        .ok_or_else(|| AppError::NotFound("Course not found".to_string()))?;
    let can_view = match role {
        "admin" => true,
        "staff_author" => course.created_by == Some(user_id) || course.status != "draft",
        "dept_reviewer" => department_id.map_or(false, |d| course.department_id == Some(d))
                           || course.status == "published",
        _ => course.status == "published",
    };
    if !can_view { return Err(AppError::Forbidden("Access denied".to_string())); }
    let tags = course_repo::get_course_tags(pool, course.id).await?;
    Ok(build_course_response(course, tags))
}
```

**`backend/src/routes/courses.rs`** — Pass user claims to get_course
```rust
let course = course_service::get_course(
    pool.inner(), &uuid, &user.claims.role, user.claims.user_id, user.claims.department_id,
).await.map_err(|e| <(Status, Json<ApiError>)>::from(e))?;
```

**`backend/src/routes/auth.rs`** — Applied ReauthRequired to change_password
```rust
use crate::middleware::reauth_guard::ReauthRequired;
// change_password now uses user: ReauthRequired instead of AuthenticatedUser
```

**`backend/src/routes/risk.rs`** — Added ReauthRequired to add_blacklist
```rust
use crate::middleware::reauth_guard::ReauthRequired;
pub async fn add_blacklist(pool, _user: AdminGuard, _reauth: ReauthRequired, body) -> ...
```

**`backend/src/routes/approvals.rs`** — HmacVerified on process_scheduled
```rust
use crate::middleware::hmac_guard::HmacVerified;
pub async fn process_scheduled(pool, _hmac: HmacVerified) -> ...
```

**`backend/src/services/webhook_service.rs`** — Real HTTP delivery with reqwest
```rust
async fn attempt_delivery(url: &str, payload: &serde_json::Value, signature: Option<&str>) -> Result<i32, String> {
    let client = reqwest::Client::builder().timeout(std::time::Duration::from_secs(10)).build()?;
    let mut builder = client.post(url).header("Content-Type", "application/json").json(payload);
    if let Some(sig) = signature { builder = builder.header("X-Webhook-Signature", sig); }
    match builder.send().await {
        Ok(resp) => Ok(resp.status().as_u16() as i32),
        Err(e) => Err(e.to_string()),
    }
}
```

**`backend/Cargo.toml`** — Added reqwest
```toml
reqwest = { version = "0.12", features = ["json"] }
```

**`API_tests/test_bookings.py`** — Added `TestBookingOwnershipEnforcement` class
- Tests student cannot cancel/reschedule faculty's booking (expect 403)
- Tests admin can cancel any booking (expect 200)

**`API_tests/test_courses.py`** — Added `TestCourseDraftVisibility` class
- Tests student cannot GET draft course by UUID (expect 403/404)
- Tests author can view own draft (expect 200)
- Tests admin can view any draft (expect 200)

**`API_tests/test_auth.py`** — Added `TestReauthEnforcement` class
- Tests change-password without prior reauth returns 403
- Tests change-password after reauth returns 400/401 (not 403 — confirms reauth gate passed)

**`proxy/Dockerfile`** (NEW) — TLS proxy with self-signed cert generation
```dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine
RUN apk add --no-cache openssl
RUN mkdir -p /etc/nginx/certs && \
    openssl req -x509 -nodes -newkey rsa:2048 \
      -keyout /etc/nginx/certs/key.pem \
      -out    /etc/nginx/certs/cert.pem \
      -days   3650 \
      -subj   "/CN=localhost/O=CampusLearn Dev/C=US" \
      -addext "subjectAltName=DNS:localhost,IP:127.0.0.1"
COPY nginx.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf
EXPOSE 80 443
```

**`proxy/nginx.conf`** (NEW) — HTTP redirect + HTTPS TLS termination
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name _;
    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/certs/cert.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/certs/key.pem;
    ssl_protocols       TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;
    ssl_ciphers         ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256:...;
    add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains" always;
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff" always;
    add_header X-Frame-Options "DENY" always;
    add_header Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin" always;
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://frontend:3000;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto https;
        # ...
